headline.main: DR. B. T. WASHINGTON, NEGRO LEADER, DEAD; Founder of the Tuskegee Institute Expires of Hardening of Arteries After Brief Illness. TAKEN TO HIS HOME TO DIE Seth Low and W. J. Willcox Persuaded Him to Consult Specialists, Who Told Him He Was Doomed. DR. B. T. WASHINGTON, NEGRO LEADER, DEAD

snippet: TUSKEGEE, Ala., Nov. 14. -- Booker T. Washington, foremost teacher and leader of the negro race, died early today at his home here, near the Tuskegee Institute, which he founded and of which he was President. Hardening of the arteries, following a...
